news.title: Link REIT buys Singapore shopping malls for $1.6 billion
news.para: "This transaction allows us to build a dedicated team in Singapore and provides a base for Link to expand further into other asset classes and strategies in Asia Pacific," Link CEO George Hongchoy said in a statement.

news.title: China Fortune Land sells property units to CR Land in debt restructuring
news.para: The deal comes as Chinese regulators encourage financially sound developers to acquire projects from debt-laden rivals to ease liquidity stress in a sector crucial to China's economy.

news.title: Now, property documents be door-delivered in Chitradurga
news.para: Two villages - Guttinadu and MR Colony under Mattada Kurubarahatti GP limits - were selected for the launch of the initiate, and e-swattu documents were delivered to 80 houses on Wednesday, the CEO said.

news.title: Flat scheme of former NIT trustee on open space: Nagpur society
news.para: Even as the inquiry is under process, a 7-storeyed residential building has come up at the spot. It has been constructed by M/s Ankit Constructions in which Kishor Kanhere, former NCP and current Shiv Sena neta, is a partner as per NIT’s note to UDD.

news.title: Kanpur development body demolishes 12-acre illegal plotting behind Chakeri Airport
news.para: ​The said plotting was being done without seeking sanction of the site plan by the KDA and it was also against the norms of UP Urban Planning and Development Act,1973.

news.title: Puravankara approves issue of NCDs worth up to Rs 230 crore
news.para: The board of directors of Puravankara also approved to invest in Ghar Realty LLP by contributing to 68.26% of the capital of the LLP as designated partner.

news.title: MahaMetro to raise Rs 3,586 crore for Nagpur Metro phase-II from ADB & EIB
news.para: Now ADB would be contributing $200 million with EIB putting in 239 million Euros for the project. The amount comes to over Rs3,500 crore. The decision was taken a few days ago.

news.title: Registration department to bifurcate Chennai zone
news.para: Tamil Nadu which has a total of 37 revenue districts is divided into 50 registration districts. The Chennai zone is divided into five registration districts comprising Chennai, Chengalpet, Kancheepuram and Tiruvallur districts.

news.title: CapitaLand India Trust to acquire Ascendas IT Park-Pune for Rs 13.5 billion
news.para: CapitaLand India Trust Management, as the trustee-manager of CLINT, entered into definitive agreements through its wholly-owned subsidiary, Ecospace IT Park for the proposed acquisition. Ascendas IT Park (Pune) owns International Tech Park Pune in Hinjawadi (ITPP-H).

news.title: Aerial survey identifies 2,500 buildings under buffer zone in Kochi
news.para: As per the state government’s recent decision, just like other local bodies which face similar issue, Kochi corporation also should conduct a survey and give a report on residential areas to be excluded from the buffer zone limits to the government.

news.title: Regularisation of plots now a click away: Punjab housing minister
news.para: The facility of regularization could be availed only by those allottees whose properties fall under the unauthorized colonies developed before March 19, 2018.

news.title: Supertech offered 9,705 flats without occupancy certificates: IRP to NCLAT
news.para: Supertech has filed an appeal before the appellate tribunal challenging the National Company Law Tribunal's (NCLT) ruling on March 25 this year, wherein it initiated insolvency proceedings against the company. The matter is pending before NCLAT.

news.title: West Bengal chief secretary sets Dec 30 deadline to clear rural housing funds
news.para: For all houses, geo-tagging has been made mandatory. Centre had approved Rs 8, 200 crore for construction of 11.3 lakh dwelling units in Bengal at the end of November.

news.title: Bengaluru: 1,443 litigations of BDA properties pending in court
news.para: The Lokayukta ordered re-list the matter on February 10, 2023. BDA Engineer Member HR Shantharajanna submitted to the Lokayukta that action is being initiated in a phased manner for removal of unauthorised occupation after verifying the pendency of litigations and court orders, if any, passed.

news.title: Homebuyers in Karnataka fight for transparency, clarity
news.para: The jurisdictional Sub-Registrar Officer (SRO) is registering the deed of declaration as required by the KAOA, but they have no authority to register with an apartment owners’ association. Promoters are inserting the by-laws of the association along with the deed of declaration for registration.​
